<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="47" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="47">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="47">
Sori protruding from the margin on distinct lobes, in one plane with lamina wings, 0.9-1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-0.8 mm, symmetric, narrowly funnelform-obovate, widest at mouth; inner indusium brown, firm, equal to outer indusium, sometimes longer, apex similar to outer indusium; outer indusium truncate or obtuse, shallowly undulate; sporangia 7-12 per sorus, capsule globose and rounded at apex, gradually narrowed toward base, indurated annulus cells 15-20, clearly unequal; spores in polar view 35-45 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, in lateral view 30-33 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="47" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="47">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="47">Philippines (Leyte, Luzon, Mindanao, Negros), Moluccas (Seram), Papua New Guinea (Manus).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="47">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="47">
Although in the shape of inner and outer indusium shape this species resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="P. H. Hovenkamp &amp; T. T. Luong" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="P. H. Hovenkamp &amp; T. T. Luong" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Saccolomataceae" genus="Orthiopteris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Orthiopteris campylura subsp. var. var. kingii" order="Polypodiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="campylura" subSpecies="var." variety="kingii">Orthiopteris campylura var. kingii</taxonomicName>
, the sori are not reflexed but usually flat even when dried. The distribution center of this variety appears to be in the Philippines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
